@Saduff -- Can I ask why you removed this and the following line?

JFYI, I've read the discussions in #10872 and romkatv/powerlevel10k#1779, but I can't piece it together. You clearly recreated the (intended) `print` behavior with `echo`, but it's not clear that you recreated whatever lines 77-78 were doing after you removed them.

I ask because my own P10K transient prompt is now broken after pulling in your commit to OMZ. When I manually add lines 77-78 back in, it is fixed.

So I'm trying to figure out whether lines 77-78 actually should *not* have been removed, versus whether I should just adapt my prompt to your changes.

@romkatv Feel free to weigh in if you're able, but this seems to be a few steps removed from P10K.

Thanks all.

@esthor 

Fix: Multiple consecutive blank lines, following Markdown documentation.
Ref: [MD012](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/v0.25.1/doc/Rules.md#md012)

I don't use this functionality, but the changes look good to me.
One thing to note: THIS BREAKS AWS CLI v1 COMPATIBILITY.

@mcornella good to merge IMHO.

